    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of large tree native to Hawaii used for carvings, dugout canoes, early surfboards, and other items; tannin extracted from the bark is used for processing leather. Few koa forests remain, because the trees have been overharvested for their attractive wood. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
